<span id="freeTextContainer14393536989082285941">This novel is like Roberto Bolano on bath salts. <br/><br/>This book houses all of the debauchery where Gravey and Flood become aware through hallucinatory violence that they are contain within this novel without a passage way of escape. The reader can go further down inside the house through the sod but can&apos;t find a way through the delusional language to leave the house either. The pages are mirrors that reflect America inside each person&apos;s home and where we reside is what we embody and reflect back from</span>
  <span id="freeText14393536989082285941" style="display:none">This novel is like Roberto Bolano on bath salts. <br /><br />This book houses all of the debauchery where Gravey and Flood become aware through hallucinatory violence that they are contain within this novel without a passage way of escape. The reader can go further down inside the house through the sod but can't find a way through the delusional language to leave the house either. The pages are mirrors that reflect America inside each person's home and where we reside is what we embody and reflect back from the LCD visuals of screens and media.</span>
