<div id="review_1154180213" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1154180213" />
    <a title="Samantha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15900550-samantha"><img alt="Samantha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1633796012p2/15900550.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1154180213?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Samantha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Samantha" href="/user/show/15900550-samantha">Samantha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1154180213" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14326227658685733755">I like Blake Butler&apos;s other work and was looking forward to this. Unfortunately, I wish I&apos;d enjoyed it more than I did. It&apos;s certainly his most ambitious work, to date, but I feel it could have been edited down quite a bit. I really was trudging through it towards the end, just wanting it to be over with. There&apos;s definitely a great smaller novel within this big one that takes chances in a very House-of-Leaves-meets-2666 way.</span>
  <span id="freeText14326227658685733755" style="display:none">I like Blake Butler's other work and was looking forward to this. Unfortunately, I wish I'd enjoyed it more than I did. It's certainly his most ambitious work, to date, but I feel it could have been edited down quite a bit. I really was trudging through it towards the end, just wanting it to be over with. There's definitely a great smaller novel within this big one that takes chances in a very House-of-Leaves-meets-2666 way.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14326227658685733755" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

